# UI defaults (skeleton + i18n)

When writing or editing UI code, apply these by default.

---

## 1. Loading state — use PrimeNG Skeleton

- Use **`<p-skeleton>`** for loading; do not add spinners or new loading flags.
- Use existing loading flags only (e.g. `loading`, `loadingDetails`, `isLoading$`).

### Mandatory rule (updated)

- **Any change in ANY component MUST include a proper skeleton state.**
- The skeleton must:
  - Match the **exact original size** of the content (height & width)
  - Preserve the **same layout structure**
  - Keep the **same spacing, gaps, padding, and margins**
  - Avoid any layout shift when switching between loading and loaded states

---

### Pattern

```html
*ngIf="loading; else realContent"
<ng-template #realContent>
```

- Skeleton replaces **only inner content**
- **Do not:**
  - Remove or change containers
  - Modify layout structure
  - Change CSS affecting spacing

---

### Correct example

If original content:

```html
<div class="card p-3 mb-3">
  <h3 class="mb-2">Title</h3>
  <p>Description</p>
</div>
```

Skeleton **must** be:

```html
<div class="card p-3 mb-3">
  <p-skeleton height="24px" class="mb-2"></p-skeleton>
  <p-skeleton height="16px" width="80%"></p-skeleton>
</div>
```

- Same container
- Same padding (`p-3`)
- Same margin (`mb-3`)
- Same spacing (`mb-2`)

---

### Wrong

- Removing wrappers
- Changing spacing
- Using random skeleton sizes
- Adding new loading flags
- Replacing full layout instead of inner content

---

### Important notes

- Do not change TypeScript logic; only change the HTML template.
- Skeleton should visually represent the final UI (shape + spacing).
- Always think: **“If skeleton disappears, layout should not move at all.”**

---

## 2. Translations — everything in en + ar

- **Templates:** All user-visible text must use:

  ```html
  {{ 'key' | translate }}
  ```

  or:

  ```html
  [placeholder]="'key' | translate"
  ```

- Add keys to **both**:
  - `src/assets/i18n/en.json`
  - `src/assets/i18n/ar.json`

---

### Toaster / notifications (MessageService)

- **Never** use hardcoded text
- **Always** use:

```ts
this.messageService.add({
  severity: 'success',
  summary: this.translate.instant('common.success'),
  detail: this.translate.instant('entityAccounts.messages.created')
});
```

---

### Arabic guidelines

- Use **formal, professional UI Arabic**
- Avoid slang or casual tone

---

## Final rule summary

Any UI change **must**:

1. Include a skeleton state
2. Match exact layout (size + spacing + structure)
3. Use existing loading flags only
4. Use translation keys (EN + AR)
5. Use translated text in toasts (no hardcoded strings)

Apply skeleton and i18n (including toasts) on every new or modified UI.
